THE CHAPTER ON THE DUTIES OF  AN ACHARYA.
SANSKRIT SLOKA:&ndash;
The noble acharya, who longs to attain the pripeval and heavenly abode of Vishnu, fights up the imperishable lamp of spiritual tradition (sampradıya) in some deserving disciple who bas been tested in various and well-known ways and fonnd fit (to receive the light). (He lights up this lamp) with true affection (sneha) when the disciple is in a state of mind (dasū) free from noworthy qualitios* (gua) like &amp; well-tested and weil-burnished vessel with oil (sucha) poured into it and with a wick (dasā) made of pure threads (guļa).
